I'm a former Blademaster and a well known reactive style addict.<br>
My question is would I &quot;gimp&quot; my Norse Savage by speccing ful H2H, 5 Savagery (just for Taunt Shout pull ability), and litterly the rest into Parry?  I've noticed I don't parry much but I do recall someone saying that the highest Savagery Parry Increase is equal to 40 spec points in Parry...of course it is only for 30seconds and you lose health.<br>
I do sort of like Savagery but nothing makes me happier then evasive defenses like evade and parry.  <br>
What if I specced full H2H and split the remainder between Parry and Savagery?  Or will this also not be worth it?  Is Savagery sort of all or nothing, I guess is part of the question.  And just how useful is it in RvR?  Any good without a healer in your company?  <br>
I'm at lvl 11 right now and in a bind trying to decide exactly what to do.  Any help would be greatly appreciated. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whipmistressbliss>Whipmistress Bliss</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/zenashes/myhomepage/bkoalt.jpg?mtbrand=AOL_US" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(3/12/03 8:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Savage Spec Question</span><hr size=1> Savagery is AWESOME in RvR.  You figure in alot fights your lifespan could be short anyways, so why not trade your HPs for 30 seconds of power.  <br>
<br>
At first, Savage really does suck, they are a class that takes alot more thought and speed than others.  You have to be very fast on the keyboard, you don't just spam a couple styles like zerkers.  If you do like a class that takes more strategy and thought though, Savage is awesome. <br>
<br>
I would recommend very very very highly against putting to much into Parry and focus on h2h and Savagery only.  Yes at first Savagery isn't that great, but trust me as you get to the 30's and 40's it begins to own all.  But, if you don't feel like you are smart or fast, you shouldn't play a Savage, stick to a zerk or something that is easier to play.  :P<br>
<br>
My spec:<br>
Parry 4<br>
Savagery 49<br>
H2H 44 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=asgrotheangry>Asgro Theangry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#000000>(3/14/03 7:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Savage Spec Question</span><hr size=1> I hate Zerks.<br>
